  "prompt": "Are there legal requirements for reporting suspected money laundering?",
  "response": "Yes, there are legal requirements for reporting suspected money laundering in many countries. Financial institutions and certain businesses are typically required to report suspicious transactions to designated authorities. These requirements vary by jurisdiction but generally involve:\n\n1. Mandatory reporting of unusual or suspicious financial activities\n2. Implementing anti-money laundering (AML) compliance programs\n3. Conducting customer due diligence\n4. Maintaining transaction records\n5. Training employees to recognize potential money laundering indicators\n\nSpecific reporting requirements depend on local laws and regulations.",
